It was shown that a hybrid approach could use the existing solutions (aperture integration) over the main beam region and the edge diffraction solutions over the remainder of the pattern. This generally gave good agreement with experiment for both the E- and H-plane patterns of horn antennas in the forward region and on the average in the low response backward region.

This equivalent current concept prediction was shown to improve the pattern level with the average measured radiation in the broad range of low response backward region.\index{Horn radiation pattern!equivalent current concept}

